name: Weedle
flavorText: Its poison stinger is very powerful. Its bright-colored body is intended to warn off its enemies.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Grass Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Kakuna
flavorText: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Beedrill
flavorText: May appear in a swarm. Flies at violent speeds, all the while stabbing with the toxic stinger on its rear.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is the last card in your hand, you may play it onto your Bench. If you do, draw 3 cards.

name: Exeggcute
flavorText: Six of them form a single Pokémon. Should one of the six be lost, the next morning there will once more be six.

name: Exeggutor
flavorText: Each of its three heads has its own thoughts. When they want to go in different directions, Exeggutor becomes unable to move.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't use that attack.

name: Yanma
flavorText: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Yanmega
flavorText: This six-legged Pokémon is easily capable of transporting an adult in flight. The wings on its tail help it stay balanced.
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Pineco
flavorText: It sticks tree bark to itself with its saliva, making itself thicker and larger. Elderly Pineco are ridiculously huge.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

name: Celebi
flavorText: This Pokémon has the ability to move through time. Records describing it as a forest deity can be found from many different eras.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.
Attack2Text: For each of your Benched Pokémon, search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Seedot
flavorText: If it remains still, it looks just like a real nut. It delights in surprising foraging Pokémon.

name: Nuzleaf
flavorText: It lives deep in forests. With the leaf on its head, it makes a flute whose song makes listeners uneasy.

name: Shiftry
flavorText: A Pokémon that was feared as a forest guardian. It can read the foe's mind and take preemptive action.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, each Supporter card in your opponent's hand has the effect "Draw 3 cards." (This happens instead of the card's usual effect.)
Attack1Text: You may have your opponent switch their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

name: Nincada
flavorText: Because it lived almost entirely underground, it is nearly blind. It uses its antennae instead.
Attack1Text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Ninjask
flavorText: Its cry leaves a lasting headache if heard for too long. It moves so quickly that it is almost invisible.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon, you may search your deck for Shedinja and put it onto your Bench. Shuffle your deck afterward.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Shaymin
flavorText: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent shuffles their Active Pokémon and all attached cards and puts them on the bottom of their deck.

name: Genesect
flavorText: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Skiddo
flavorText: If it has sunshine and water, it doesn't need to eat, because it can generate energy from the leaves on its back.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Grass Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Gogoat
flavorText: They inhabit mountainous regions. The leader of the herd is decided by a battle of clashing horns.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Dhelmise
flavorText: After a piece of seaweed merged with debris from a sunken ship, it was reborn as this ghost Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

name: Orbeetle V
Attack1Text: You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Orbeetle VMAX
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Pokémon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Zarude V
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: You may attach up to 2 basic Energy cards from your hand to your Benched Pokémon in any way you like. If you attached Energy to a Pokémon in this way, heal all damage from that Pokémon.

name: Charmander
flavorText: It has a preference for hot things. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Charmeleon
flavorText: It has a barbaric nature. In battle, it whips its fiery tail around and slashes away with sharp claws.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck.

name: Charizard
flavorText: It spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. It may cause forest fires by blowing flames.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may look at the top 3 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Discard the other cards.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Leon card in your discard pile.

name: Flareon
flavorText: Once it has stored up enough heat, this Pokémon's body temperature can reach up to 1,700 degrees Fahrenheit.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has a Memory Capsule attached, Grass Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

name: Slugma
flavorText: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn't keep moving, its body will cool and harden.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Magcargo
flavorText: Its body is as hot as lava and is always billowing. Flames will occasionally burst from its shell.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Talonflame V
Attack1Text: If you go first, you can use this attack during your first turn. Discard your hand and draw 6 cards.
Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Vaporeon
flavorText: When Vaporeon's fins begin to vibrate, it is a sign that rain will come within a few hours.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has a Memory Capsule attached, Fire Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

name: Wailmer
flavorText: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Wailord
flavorText: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.
Ability1Text: Whenever you attach an Energy card from your hand to this Pokémon, remove all Special Conditions from it.
Attack1Text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

name: Oshawott
flavorText: It fights using the scalchop on its stomach. In response to an attack, it retaliates immediately by slashing.

name: Dewott
flavorText: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.
Attack2Text: You may put an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon into their hand.

name: Samurott
flavorText: One swing of the sword incorporated in its armor can fell an opponent. A simple glare from one of them quiets everybody.
Ability1Text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: You may put 2 Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon into their hand.

name: Galarian Darmanitan V
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Galarian Darmanitan VMAX
Attack1Text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Chewtle
flavorText: Apparently the itch of its teething impels it to snap its jaws at anything in front of it.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

name: Drednaw
flavorText: With jaws that can shear through steel rods, this highly aggressive Pokémon chomps down on its unfortunate prey.
Attack1Text: If you played Nessa from your hand during this turn, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Cramorant
flavorText: Cramorant's gluttony led it to try to swallow an Arrokuda whole, which in turn led to Cramorant getting an Arrokuda stuck in its throat.
Attack1Text: Discard any number of Arrokuda from your Bench. This attack does 60 damage for each Arrokuda you discarded in this way.

name: Arrokuda
flavorText: If it sees any movement around it, this Pokémon charges for it straightaway, leading with its sharply pointed jaw. It's very proud of that jaw.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Arrokuda and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Barraskewda
flavorText: This Pokémon has a jaw that's as sharp as a spear and as strong as steel. Apparently Barraskewda's flesh is surprisingly tasty, too.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon for each damage counter on that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Pikachu V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Lightning Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Pikachu VMAX
Attack1Text: You may discard all Energy from this Pokémon. If you do, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Voltorb
flavorText: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a Poké Ball, it has zapped many people.

name: Electrode
flavorText: It stores an overflowing amount of electric energy inside its body. Even a small shock makes it explode.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may search your deck for up to 2 Lightning Energy cards and attach them to your Lightning Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck. If you searched your deck in this way, this Pokémon is Knocked Out.

name: Jolteon
flavorText: If it is angered or startled, the fur all over its body bristles like sharp needles that pierce foes.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has a Memory Capsule attached, Water Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.

name: Zapdos
flavorText: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon, and this attack does 160 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon V or Pokémon-GX. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Ampharos V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon that has any damage counters on it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Raikou
flavorText: This rough Pokémon stores energy inside its body, then sweeps across the land, shooting off electricity.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Electrike
flavorText: It stores static electricity in its fur for discharging. It gives off sparks if a storm approaches.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Manectric
flavorText: It stimulates its own muscles with electricity, so it can move quickly. It eases its soreness with electricity, too, so it can recover quickly as well.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may draw 3 cards.

name: Blitzle
flavorText: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

name: Zebstrika
flavorText: They have lightning-like movements. When Zebstrika run at full speed, the sound of thunder reverberates.

name: Joltik
flavorText: Joltik can be found clinging to other Pokémon. It's soaking up static electricity because it can't produce a charge on its own.

name: Galvantula
flavorText: It launches electrified fur from its abdomen as its means of attack. Opponents hit by the fur could be in for three full days and nights of paralysis.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Tynamo
flavorText: One alone can emit only trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.
Ability1Text: If this Pokémon has any Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

name: Eelektrik
flavorText: These Pokémon have a big appetite. When they spot their prey, they attack it and paralyze it with electricity.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

name: Eelektross
flavorText: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if they attach an Energy card from their hand to the Defending Pokémon, put 6 damage counters on that Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokémon and 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Zekrom
flavorText: When the interior part of its tail spins like a motor, Zekrom can generate many bolts of lightning to blast its surroundings.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 60 damage to itself. Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Zeraora
flavorText: It runs as fast as lightning strikes, shredding its opponents with its high-voltage claws.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon V or Pokémon-GX, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Pincurchin
flavorText: It feeds on seaweed, using its teeth to scrape it off rocks. Electric current flows from the tips of its spines.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Clefairy
flavorText: It is said that happiness will come to those who see a gathering of Clefairy dancing under a full moon.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Clefable
flavorText: A timid fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen, it will run and hide the moment it senses people.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if your Active Pokémon has any Psychic Energy attached, you may heal 20 damage from it, and it recovers from a Special Condition.

name: Girafarig
flavorText: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on your opponent's Pokémon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: You may have your opponent shuffle their hand into their deck. If you do, your opponent draws 4 cards.

name: Shedinja
flavorText: A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a Poké Ball when a Nincada evolves.
Ability1Text: Put this Pokémon into play only with the effect of Ninjask's Cast-Off Shell Ability. (When you are setting up to play, you cannot put it face down as your Active Pokémon or on your Bench.)
Attack1Text: Put damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon until its remaining HP is 10.

name: Shuppet
flavorText: There's a proverb that says, "Shun the house where Shuppet gather in the growing dusk."
Attack1Text: Put 1 damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Banette
flavorText: Resentment at being cast off made it spring into being. Some say that treating it well will satisfy it, and it will once more become a stuffed toy.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may devolve 1 of your opponent's Benched evolved Pokémon by putting the highest Stage Evolution card on it into your opponent's hand.

name: Duskull
flavorText: If it finds bad children who won't listen to their parents, it will spirit them away—or so it's said.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 4 cards of either player's deck and put them back in any order.

name: Dusclops
flavorText: Its body is entirely hollow. When it opens its mouth, it sucks everything in as if it were a black hole.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Dusknoir
flavorText: At the bidding of transmissions from the spirit world, it steals people and Pokémon away. No one knows whether it has a will of its own.
Ability1Text: All Special Energy attached to Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) provide Colorless Energy and have no other effect.

name: Chimecho
flavorText: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Pokémon and a Supporter card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

name: Woobat
flavorText: While inside a cave, if you look up and see lots of heart-shaped marks lining the walls, it's evidence that Woobat live there.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) If you have any cards in your hand, this attack does nothing.

name: Swoobat
flavorText: Emitting powerful sound waves tires it out. Afterward, it won't be able to fly for a little while.
Ability1Text: Prevent all effects of your opponent's attacks, except damage, done to this Pokémon.

name: Cottonee
flavorText: It shoots cotton from its body to protect itself. If it gets caught up in hurricane-strength winds, it can get sent to the other side of the Earth.

name: Whimsicott
flavorText: It scatters cotton all over the place as a prank. If it gets wet, it'll become too heavy to move and have no choice but to answer for its mischief.
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: Before doing damage, you may discard any number of Pokémon Tools from your Pokémon. This attack does 40 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Dedenne
flavorText: Its upper whiskers are sensors that survey its surroundings. Its lower whiskers are organs that shoot electricity.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Xerneas
flavorText: When the horns on its head shine in seven different colors, it is said to be sharing everlasting life.
Attack1Text: Put a card from your discard pile into your hand.
Attack2Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

name: Diancie
flavorText: It can instantly create many diamonds by compressing the carbon in the air between its hands.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, any damage done to your Pokémon by an opponent's attack is reduced by 30 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: If you played a Supporter card from your hand during this turn, this attack does 70 more damage.

name: Milcery
flavorText: This Pokémon was born from sweet-smelling particles in the air. Its body is made of cream.
Attack1Text: Heal 20 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

name: Alcremie
flavorText: When it trusts a Trainer, it will treat them to berries it's decorated with cream.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may have each player draw a card.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Zacian
flavorText: Now armed with a weapon it used in ancient times, this Pokémon needs only a single strike to fell even Gigantamax Pokémon.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent has any Pokémon VMAX in play, this attack does 150 more damage.

name: Wooper
flavorText: This Pokémon lives in cold water. It will leave the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

name: Quagsire
flavorText: It has an easygoing nature. It doesn't care if it bumps its head on boats and boulders while swimming.
Attack2Text: If you have exactly 2, 4, or 6 Prize cards remaining, this attack does nothing.

name: Shuckle
flavorText: It stores berries inside its shell. To avoid attacks, it hides beneath rocks and remains completely still.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

name: Phanpy
flavorText: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

name: Donphan
flavorText: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.
Attack1Text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Hitmontop
flavorText: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.
Attack1Text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: If you played Bea from your hand during this turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Regirock
flavorText: The same rocks that form its body have been found in ground layers around the world.
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Riolu
flavorText: It's exceedingly energetic, with enough stamina to keep running all through the night. Taking it for walks can be a challenging experience.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Drilbur
flavorText: It brings its claws together and whirls around at high speed before rushing toward its prey.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Terrakion
flavorText: It has phenomenal power. It will mercilessly crush anyone or anything that bullies small Pokémon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack2Text: If you have a Stadium in play, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: Born when all of Zygarde's cells have been gathered together, it uses force to neutralize those who harm the ecosystem.
Attack2Text: If you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Rockruff
flavorText: When it rubs the rocks on its neck against you, that's proof of its love for you. However, the rocks are sharp, so the gesture is quite painful!

name: Lycanroc
flavorText: They live alone without forming packs. They will only listen to orders from Trainers who can draw out their true power.

name: Mudbray
flavorText: Loads weighing up to 50 times as much as its own body weight pose no issue for this Pokémon. It's skilled at making use of mud.

name: Mudsdale
flavorText: Mud that hardens around a Mudsdale's legs sets harder than stone. It's so hard that it allows this Pokémon to scrap a truck with a single kick.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 less damage for each Colorless in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

name: Coalossal V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

name: Coalossal VMAX
Attack1Text: Discard the top card of your deck. If that card is an Energy card, this attack does 90 more damage, and attach that card to this Pokémon.

name: Clobbopus
flavorText: It's very curious, but its means of investigating things is to try to punch them with its tentacles. The search for food is what brings it onto land.

name: Grapploct
flavorText: A body made up of nothing but muscle makes the grappling moves this Pokémon performs with its tentacles tremendously powerful.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.
Attack2Text: If this Pokémon used Full Nelson during your last turn, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Zamazenta
flavorText: Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master's Shield. It was feared and respected by all.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from Pokémon VMAX.

name: Poochyena
flavorText: It has a very tenacious nature. Its acute sense of smell lets it chase a chosen prey without ever losing track.

name: Mightyena
flavorText: It chases down prey in a pack of around ten. They defeat foes with perfectly coordinated teamwork.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon's attacks do 50 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Sableye
flavorText: This Pokémon is feared. When its gemstone eyes begin to glow with a sinister shine, it's believed that Sableye will steal people's spirits away.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't use that attack.

name: Drapion V
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon. Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed and Poisoned.

name: Sandile
flavorText: Sandile's still not good at hunting, so it mostly eats things that have collapsed in the desert. It's called "the cleaner of the desert."
Attack1Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Krokorok
flavorText: It buries some of its prey in the sand to use as emergency meals when its hunts are unsuccessful.
Attack2Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.

name: Krookodile
flavorText: It conceals itself in sandstorms that Flygon whip up and waits patiently for prey to appear.
Attack1Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Trubbish
flavorText: Its favorite places are unsanitary ones. If you leave trash lying around, you could even find one of these Pokémon living in your room.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Garbodor
flavorText: This Pokémon eats trash, which turns into poison inside its body. The main component of the poison depends on what sort of trash was eaten.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokémon Tool card in your discard pile. Then, shuffle those cards into your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

name: Galarian Meowth
flavorText: Living with a savage, seafaring people has toughened this Pokémon's body so much that parts of it have turned to iron.
Attack2Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Galarian Perrserker
flavorText: What appears to be an iron helmet is actually hardened hair. This Pokémon lives for the thrill of battle.
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. If any of them are heads, your opponent reveals their hand. Then, for each heads, discard a Trainer card from your opponent's hand.

name: Forretress
flavorText: In the moment that it gulps down its prey, the inside of its shell is exposed, but to this day, no one has ever seen that sight.
Attack1Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.
Attack2Text: Both Active Pokémon are Knocked Out.

name: Steelix V
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.
Attack2Text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Beldum
flavorText: If you anger it, it will do more than rampage. It will also burst out strong magnetism, causing nearby machines to break.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Metang
flavorText: It flies at high speeds around the skies. When it finds its prey, Metang takes a firm grip with its sharp claws and never lets go.

name: Metagross
flavorText: It analyzes its opponents with more accuracy than a supercomputer, which enables it to calmly back them into a corner.
Ability1Text: Your Pokémon in play have no Retreat Cost.
Attack1Text: If the Defending Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Jirachi
flavorText: Once every 1,000 years, the singing of a pure voice will rouse this Pokémon from its near-perpetual slumber. It wakes for only seven days.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Put the other card back on top of your deck.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 7 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Lucario
flavorText: It controls waves known as auras, which are powerful enough to pulverize huge rocks. It uses these waves to take down its prey.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Dialga
flavorText: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Metal Energy cards from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokémon.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Excadrill
flavorText: It's not uncommon for tunnels that appear to have formed naturally to actually be a result of Excadrill's rampant digging.
Attack1Text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Ferroseed
flavorText: It defends itself by launching spikes, but its aim isn't very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Ferrothorn
flavorText: This Pokémon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.

name: Galarian Stunfisk
flavorText: Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.

name: Aegislash V

name: Aegislash VMAX

name: Magearna

Attack2Text: This attack does 20 more damage for each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon.

name: Duraludon
flavorText: Its body resembles polished metal, and it's both lightweight and strong. The only drawback is that it rusts easily.

Attack2Text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Eevee
evolvesTo: Vaporeon, Jolteon, Flareon, Sylveon, Espeon, Umbreon, Leafeon, Glaceon
flavorText: It has the ability to alter the composition of its body to suit its surrounding environment.

name: Snorlax
flavorText: It is not satisfied unless it eats over 880 pounds of food every day. When it is done eating, it goes promptly to sleep.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

name: Lugia
flavorText: It is said to be the guardian of the seas. It is rumored to have been seen on the night of a storm.
Attack2Text: If your opponent has 5 or fewer cards in their hand, this attack does nothing.

name: Taillow
flavorText: It dislikes cold seasons. They migrate to other lands in search of warmth, flying over 180 miles a day.

name: Swellow

name: Whismur
flavorText: If it senses danger, it scares the foe by crying out with the volume of a jet-plane engine.

flavorText: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each of your Pokémon in play that has the Round attack.

name: Exploud
flavorText: Its roar in battle shakes the ground like a tremor—or like an earthquake has struck.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage for each of your Pokémon in play that has the Round attack.

name: Rayquaza
flavorText: It flies in the ozone layer, way up high in the sky. Until recently, no one had ever seen it.

name: Chatot
flavorText: It can learn and speak human words. If they gather, they all learn the same saying.

name: Togekiss VMAX
Attack1Text: You may search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Pikipek
flavorText: It may look spindly, but its neck muscles are heavy-duty. It can peck at a tree 16 times per second!

name: Trumbeak

Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: It knows the forest inside and out. If it comes across a wounded Pokémon, Oranguru will gather medicinal herbs to treat it.
